		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">philexile wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Sorry to dig up an old post. I'm a new PowerPak owner and I did the resistor mod. I too noticed that the VRC6 channel is too loud in Akumajō Densetsu. You can barely hear the whip noise overtop of it. Anyone else notice that?</div>
<br />
<br />I got a 100k potentiometer and used that in place of the 47k resistor.  That way you can change the volume to whatever level you want (i matched mine to an emulator's vrc6 levels using a wave editor).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
